{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775867627922,"sessionID":"ses_28610dbaeffepLJg4zy3RXuxvc","part":{"id":"prt_d79f16355001NtCjDaAYeQjllt","messageID":"msg_d79f1336c001g8YNCmrXxGvpqL","sessionID":"ses_28610dbaeffepLJg4zy3RXuxvc","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-013 Tasks: Redis 存储实现 (Redis Storage Implementation)\n\n## Overview\n- **AR:** AR-013\n- **Module:** pkg/store\n- **Language:** Go\n- **Size:** M\n- **Status:** Stage ST-3 (Design) Completed\n- **Base Spec:** AR-012 (Store Interface Definition)\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### T1: Redis Store Implementation - Core Structure [PENDING]\n- [ ] Create `pkg/store/redis.go` with `redisStore` struct\n- [ ] Define `redisOptions` struct with `Addr` and `Password` fields\n- [ ] Implement `newRedisStore()` constructor with environment parsing\n- [ ] Implement `makeRedisOptions()` for `REDIS_ADDR`, `REDIS_PASSWORD`, `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED`\n- [ ] Add `sessionKey()` helper method for key construction (`session:` + sessionID)\n- **Verification:** File compiles; `go build ./pkg/store/...` succeeds\n- **Files:** `pkg/store/redis.go`\n\n### T2: Redis Store - Ping Method [PENDING]\n- [ ] Implement `Ping(ctx context.Context) error`\n- [ ] Issue `PING` command via go-redis/v9 client\n- [ ] Validate response is exactly `\"PONG\"`\n- [ ] Return error on connection failure or unexpected response\n- **Verification:** Unit test passes with mocked Redis client\n- **Files:** `pkg/store/redis.go`, `pkg/store/redis_test.go`\n\n### T3: Redis Store - GetSandboxBySessionID [PENDING]\n- [ ] Implement `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n- [ ] Validate empty sessionID returns error before querying\n- [ ] Execute `GET session:{id}` command\n- [ ] Translate `redisv9.Nil` to `ErrNotFound`\n- [ ] Unmarshal JSON response to `*types.SandboxInfo`\n- [ ] Return wrapped error on JSON parse failure\n- **Verification:** Test missing key returns `ErrNotFound`; test valid session returns data\n- **Files:** `pkg/store/redis.go`, `pkg/store/redis_test.go`\n\n### T4: Redis Store - StoreSandbox [PENDING]\n- [ ] Implement `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error`\n- [ ] Validate nil sandbox returns error (no Redis commands)\n- [ ] Validate empty `SessionID` returns error (no Redis commands)\n- [ ] Validate zero `ExpiresAt` returns error (no Redis commands)\n- [ ] Marshal sandbox to JSON\n- [ ] Use Pipeline for atomic operation:\n  - `SETNX session:{id} {json}`\n  - `ZADD session:expiry {ExpiresAt.Unix()} {id}`\n  - `ZADD session:last_activity {Now.Unix()} {id}`\n- [ ] Check `SETNX` result; if false, return \"session already exists\" error\n- [ ] Return pipeline execution error if any command fails\n- **Verification:** Test validation errors (no Redis calls); test atomic success; test duplicate session\n- **Files:** `pkg/store/redis.go`, `pkg/store/redis_test.go`\n\n### T5: Redis Store - UpdateSandbox [PENDING]\n- [ ] Implement `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error`\n- [ ] Validate nil sandbox returns error\n- [ ] Validate empty `SessionID` returns error\n- [ ] Marshal sandbox to JSON\n- [ ] Execute `SET session:{id} {json} XX` (key must exist)\n- [ ] If result is false, return \"key not exists\" error\n- [ ] Do NOT modify expiry or activity ZSETs\n- **Verification:** Test missing key returns error; test successful update\n- **Files:** `pkg/store/redis.go`, `pkg/store/redis_test.go`\n\n### T6: Redis Store - DeleteSandboxBySessionID [PENDING]\n- [ ] Implement `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID string) error`\n- [ ] Validate empty sessionID returns error (no Redis commands)\n- [ ] Use Pipeline for atomic operation:\n  - `DEL session:{id}`\n  - `ZREM session:expiry {id}`\n  - `ZREM session:last_activity {id}`\n- [ ] Return pipeline execution error\n- **Verification:** Test deletion removes all keys; test empty ID validation\n- **Files:** `pkg/store/redis.go`, `pkg/store/redis_test.go`\n\n### T7: Redis Store - ListExpiredSandboxes [PENDING]\n- [ ] Implement `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n- [ ] Return `nil, nil` if limit <= 0 (no Redis query)\n- [ ] Execute `ZRANGE session:expiry -inf {before.Unix()} BYSCORE LIMIT 0 {limit}`\n- [ ] Call `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs()` helper to fetch full documents\n- **Verification:** Test limit=0 returns empty; test expired sessions returned\n- **Files:** `pkg/store/redis.go`, `pkg/store/redis_test.go`\n\n### T8: Redis Store - ListInactiveSandboxes [PENDING]\n- [ ] Implement `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n- [ ] Return `nil, nil` if limit <= 0 (no Redis query)\n- [ ] Execute `ZRANGE session:last_activity -inf {before.Unix()} BYSCORE LIMIT 0 {limit}`\n- [ ] Call `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs()` helper to fetch full documents\n- **Verification:** Test limit=0 returns empty; test inactive sessions returned\n- **Files:** `pkg/store/redis.go`, `pkg/store/redis_test.go`\n\n### T9: Redis Store - Helper: loadSandboxesBySessionIDs [PENDING]\n- [ ] Implement `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx context.Context, sessionIDs []string) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n- [ ] Return empty slice if sessionIDs is empty\n- [ ] Construct keys using `sessionKey()` for each sessionID\n- [ ] Execute `MGET` for all keys\n- [ ] Iterate results and skip nil/invalid entries (orphan tolerance)\n- [ ] Unmarshal valid JSON to `*types.SandboxInfo`\n- [ ] Return slice of valid sandboxes\n- **Verification:** Test orphaned entries are skipped; test batch loading\n- **Files:** `pkg/store/redis.go`, `pkg/store/redis_test.go`\n\n### T10: Redis Store - UpdateSessionLastActivity [PENDING]\n- [ ] Implement `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID string, at time.Time) error`\n- [ ] Validate empty sessionID returns error (no Redis query)\n- [ ] Execute `EXISTS session:{id}` to verify session exists\n- [ ] Return `ErrNotFound` if exists == 0\n- [ ] If `at.IsZero()`, use `time.Now()`\n- [ ] Execute `ZADD session:last_activity {at.Unix()} {sessionID}`\n- **Verification:** Test missing session returns `ErrNotFound`; test zero time uses now\n- **Files:** `pkg/store/redis.go`, `pkg/store/redis_test.go`\n\n### T11: Redis Store - Close [PENDING]\n- [ ] Implement `Close() error`\n- [ ] Call `s.cli.Close()` on Redis client\n- [ ] Return the error from Close()\n- **Verification:** Test Close releases connection\n- **Files:** `pkg/store/redis.go`, `pkg/store/redis_test.go`\n\n### T12: Valkey Store Implementation - Core Structure [PENDING]\n- [ ] Create `pkg/store/valkey.go` with `valkeyStore` struct\n- [ ] Define `valkeyOptions` struct with `InitAddress []string`, `Password`, `DisableCache`, `ForceSingleClient`\n- [ ] Implement `newValkeyStore()` constructor\n- [ ] Implement `makeValkeyOptions()` for Valkey environment parsing\n- **Verification:** File compiles; `go build ./pkg/store/...` succeeds\n- **Files:** `pkg/store/valkey.go`\n\n### T13: Valkey Store - Ping Method [PENDING]\n- [ ] Implement `Ping(ctx context.Context) error`\n- [ ] Build command using `B().Ping().Build()`\n- [ ] Validate response is exactly `\"PONG\"`\n- **Verification:** Unit test passes with mocked Valkey client\n- **Files:** `pkg/store/valkey.go`, `pkg/store/valkey_test.go`\n\n### T14: Valkey Store - GetSandboxBySessionID [PENDING]\n- [ ] Implement `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n- [ ] Validate empty sessionID returns error before querying\n- [ ] Build GET command using valkey-go builder\n- [ ] Detect `IsValkeyNil` error and translate to `ErrNotFound`\n- [ ] Unmarshal JSON response\n- **Verification:** Test missing key returns `ErrNotFound`\n- **Files:** `pkg/store/valkey.go`, `pkg/store/valkey_test.go`\n\n### T15: Valkey Store - StoreSandbox [PENDING]\n- [ ] Implement `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error`\n- [ ] Validate nil sandbox, empty SessionID, zero ExpiresAt (no Valkey commands)\n- [ ] Marshal sandbox to JSON\n- [ ] Use `DoMulti` for atomic operation:\n  - `SET session:{id} {json} NX`\n  - `ZADD session:expiry {expires_unix} {id}`\n  - `ZADD session:last_activity {now_unix} {id}`\n- [ ] Check first result for \"OK\"; if not, return \"session already exists\"\n- **Verification:** Test validation; test atomic success; test duplicate\n- **Files:** `pkg/store/valkey.go`, `pkg/store/valkey_test.go`\n\n### T16: Valkey Store - UpdateSandbox [PENDING]\n- [ ] Implement `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error`\n- [ ] Validate nil sandbox, empty SessionID\n- [ ] Marshal sandbox to JSON\n- [ ] Execute `SET session:{id} {json} XX`\n- [ ] If result is not \"OK\", return \"key not exists\" error\n- [ ] Do NOT modify ZSETs\n- **Verification:** Test missing key returns error\n- **Files:** `pkg/store/valkey.go`, `pkg/store/valkey_test.go`\n\n### T17: Valkey Store - DeleteSandboxBySessionID [PENDING]\n- [ ] Implement `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID string) error`\n- [ ] Validate empty sessionID returns error\n- [ ] Use `DoMulti` for atomic operation:\n  - `DEL session:{id}`\n  - `ZREM session:expiry {id}`\n  - `ZREM session:last_activity {id}`\n- **Verification:** Test deletion removes all keys\n- **Files:** `pkg/store/valkey.go`, `pkg/store/valkey_test.go`\n\n### T18: Valkey Store - List Methods [PENDING]\n- [ ] Implement `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n- [ ] Return `nil, nil` if limit <= 0\n- [ ] Execute `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:expiry -inf {before.Unix()} LIMIT 0 {limit}`\n- [ ] Load full documents via batch GET\n- [ ] Implement `ListInactiveSandboxes()` similarly using `session:last_activity`\n- [ ] Implement valkey-specific `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs()` helper\n- **Verification:** Test listing with orphaned entry tolerance\n- **Files:** `pkg/store/valkey.go`, `pkg/store/valkey_test.go`\n\n### T19: Valkey Store - UpdateSessionLastActivity [PENDING]\n- [ ] Implement `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID string, at time.Time) error`\n- [ ] Validate empty sessionID\n- [ ] Execute `EXISTS session:{id}`; return `ErrNotFound` if not exists\n- [ ] If `at.IsZero()`, use `time.Now()`\n- [ ] Execute `ZADD session:last_activity {at.Unix()} {sessionID}`\n- **Verification:** Test missing session returns `ErrNotFound`\n- **Files:** `pkg/store/valkey.go`, `pkg/store/valkey_test.go`\n\n### T20: Valkey Store - Close [PENDING]\n- [ ] Implement `Close() error`\n- [ ] Call `s.cli.Close()` on Valkey client\n- [ ] Return nil on success\n- **Verification:** Test Close releases connection\n- **Files:** `pkg/store/valkey.go`, `pkg/store/valkey_test.go`\n\n### T21: Singleton Pattern & Provider Selection [PENDING]\n- [ ] Create `pkg/store/singleton.go`\n- [ ] Implement `initStore()` with `STORE_TYPE` case-insensitive parsing\n- [ ] Default to `\"redis\"` if `STORE_TYPE` unset\n- [ ] Implement `newRedisStore()` call for `redis` type\n- [ ] Implement `newValkeyStore()` call for `valkey` type\n- [ ] Return error for unsupported store type\n- [ ] Implement `Storage()` with `sync.Once` singleton pattern\n- [ ] Call `klog.Fatalf` on initialization failure\n- **Verification:** Test concurrent access returns same instance; test provider selection\n- **Files:** `pkg/store/singleton.go`, `pkg/store/singleton_test.go`\n\n### T22: Unit Tests - Redis Implementation [PENDING]\n- [ ] Test `Ping()` success and failure scenarios\n- [ ] Test `GetSandboxBySessionID()` returns `ErrNotFound` for missing key\n- [ ] Test `GetSandboxBySessionID()` rejects empty sessionID\n- [ ] Test `StoreSandbox()` validation (nil, empty ID, zero ExpiresAt)\n- [ ] Test `StoreSandbox()` atomic pipeline execution\n- [ ] Test `StoreSandbox()` fails on duplicate session\n- [ ] Test `UpdateSandbox()` XX flag behavior (missing key fails)\n- [ ] Test `DeleteSandboxBySessionID()` removes all keys\n- [ ] Test `DeleteSandboxBySessionID()` rejects empty sessionID\n- [ ] Test `ListExpiredSandboxes()`